brook /brʊk/

(brooked,brooking,brooks) 

1. N-COUNT A brook is a small stream. 小溪 

2. V-T If someone in a position of authority will brook no interference or opposition, they will not accept any interference or opposition from others. 允许 

例： From childhood on, she'd had a plan of action, one that would brook no interference. 从儿时起，她已有了一个行动计划，不容干预。

